race.comment: OAK PARK MADDISON (9) is close to breaking through. Went forward from the low draw last time and fought hard to miss narrowly. Form has stuck up strongly in 27 days and she draws well again. Looks the one to beat. ORLOVA (10) stuck on soundly into a midfield finish when resuming in town last time. Is sure to have come on from that and will appreciate the rise in trip. Big threat under the light weight of the claim. MR ZEUS (3) has given a bold sight in his two runs back, only to get reeled in. Drops back in trip and gets the blinkers on first time. Will prove stiffer to catch this time from the front. PEPPERS HOPE (7) exceeded market expectations first-up and deserves more respect this time.
